  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Send Vulnerable Filipino Children to School</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Opportunities for schooling taken for granted elsewhere are not always available to children in remote rural areas in the Philippines.  FPVI enables high school-age children who have been abandoned or are in extreme need, in the town of Tunga, in Leyte province, Philippines, to continue their education through assistance with school fees, school lunches, transportation, homework and project support, as well as counselling and monitoring of the children&apos;s general well-being.</narrative>
  </description>
